|[[Mind & Body]]
|''Work on self-improvement''
|
* Acting Lessons
* Book (''Find a good book''): The player is given a selection of seven different books varying in length. After choosing a book, a tab states the title, the author, the genre, and the amount of pages it has. Tapping the book flips one page. After tapping it as much as the number of pages in the book, you can finish the book, which increases your smarts and happiness. You can also choose to abandon the book or pick a different book, as well as watching the movie the book is associated with, which requires you to watch an ad if you don't have Bitizenship. Finishing the dictionary prompts the [[Achievements|achievement]] "Human Dictionary".
* Diet
* Gardening
* Gym
* Instruments: You can pay to take lessons to learn how to play certain instruments, or ask your parents to let your character take instrument lessons, which they can decline if they have little money or if you already play a lot of different instruments. After taking a lesson, your skill on the instrument would improve/worsen (which happens if you take too many lessons in the same year), and your parents can buy you instruments if you are under 18. When the skill bar is full, you "master" it. These are all the different instruments you can choose to take lessons on:
